    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-17T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-17T10:00:00-05:00" n="341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/13253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-17T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 17, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 18—1:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>895. Apropos of the announcement of General Weygand’s appointment as Governor
                    General of Algeria in addition to his other offices, Rochat remarked this
                    afternoon that the appointment was “pleasing to all concerned”: Weygand is given
                    “more direct control thereby in Algeria and Admiral Darlan (as Minister of the
                    Interior) will now have some direct authority over the General.”</p>
                <p>Admiral Abrial,<note n="45a" xml:id="d341fn45a">Adm. Jean Marie Abrial, former
                        Governor General of Algeria.</note> whose elimination from Algeria did not
                    come as a surprise here, is reputedly slated to be Prefect of the Seine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
